title: 820-01958 dead unable to put into DFU mode
message:
Hi I got an  820-01958. PPBUS_G3H is 12.6v, PP5V_G3S is 5v, PP3V3_G3H is 3.3v. PVDDCPUAWAKE_SW0 to SW3 are 0.75v, PP0V82_SLPDDR is 0.82v, PP1V8_SLPS2R is 1.8v, , PP1V1_SLPS2R is 1.1v, PP0V9_SLPDDR is 0.9v, PPVCCQ_ANI_SSD0 is 1.8v. PP1V05_PCH_EXT_REG, PPVNN_PCH_EXT_REG, and PPVCC_CPU_PH1 to PH3 are all present when the unit is undergoing a DFU. DFU fails with either 4010, or 4017. We've noticed that Y8001 reads 33-34Khz and increases to 42Khz during a DFU.

I also tried looking for dump of  U4770 but am unable to find one. Any input appreciated.

title: 820-01958 dead unable to put into DFU mode
message:
If machine cannot complete DFU, should be a problem with T2, or SSD.

Any history available, liquid sign?
Check for liquid sign at audio board and flex.

title: 820-01958 dead unable to put into DFU mode
message: I checked the audio board on the machine, it's perfectly clean. There was some liquid damage from hot chocolate on the board around Q7660 which has been cleared, and near C6481.

title: 820-01958 dead unable to put into DFU mode
message: Would there be any point in trying a known working dump of the SoC ROM? If so would anyone have one available?

title: 820-01958 dead unable to put into DFU mode
message:
I don't have SoC ROM dump for this board.
People say on Internet they solved not turning board on Internet on this way.
However, I'm not sure about this.

Personally I swapped a dump from good working 01521 board to other, which turned on too, but had other issue.
Aftewr that, the board didn't even switch to 20V; using tested dump, good 100%.
